register.description: This register contains the IP revision code.(A write or reset of to this register has no effect.)
This register allows controlling various parameters of the OCP interface.

bitfield.description: OCP Clock activity when module is in IDLE mode (during wake up mode period)

bitenum.description: OCP Clock is maintained during wake up period

bitfield.description: Slave interface power management (IDLE req/ack control)

bitenum.description: FORCE Idle. IDLE request is acknowledged unconditionally and immediately(Default Dumb mode for safety)
NO idle. IDLE request is never acknowledged.
SMART Idle. The acknowledgment to an IDLE request is given based on the internal activity.

bitfield.description: Module software resetThis bit is automatically reset by hardware (During reads, it always returns 0.)It has same effect as the OCP hardware reset.
Internal OCP clock gating strategy(no module visible impact other than saving power)

bitenum.description: Automatic internal OCP clock gating strategy is applied based on the OCP interface activity.

register.description: Internal reset monitoring (OCP domain)Undefined since:From hardware perspective, the reset state is 0.From software user perspective, when the accessible module is 1.

bitfield.description: Internal reset monitoring (OCP domain)Undefined since:From hardware perspective, the reset state is 0.From software user perspective, when the accessible module is 1.
